serverInfo: typeof MCP_SERVER_INFO;\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:4:MCP Mock Server is a public remote MCP mock server and web UI for testing no-auth, Basic Auth, and mock OAuth bearer tool calls.\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:8:MCP client developers, AI agent developers, demo/QA users, and the server operator.\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:11:MCP client and AI-agent developers need a configurable remote server that behaves enough like a real MCP server to prove connection, auth, token, permission, and tool-call behavior before integrating with production systems.\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:14:Remote MCP adoption is moving auth, transport, and permission bugs into client integration work. A public mock server gives teams a repeatable target for manual testing, automated E2E checks, demos, and negative-path validation.\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:17:- realistic MCP and OAuth behavior over decorative admin features\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:25:- create a mock endpoint once and exercise it through MCP and REST\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:26:- inspect the generated MCP input schema and execute REST no-auth or Basic calls from the endpoint console with raw evidence\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:27:- initialize no-auth MCP clients, list enabled tools, and execute exact-match tool calls\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:29:- list enabled tools and call configured mock tools through simple REST routes for curl and Postman style testing\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:30:- prove no-auth, Basic, and OAuth bearer client behavior against strict routes\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:31:- issue mock OAuth tokens with endpoint-level permissions through browser consent or non-interactive client credentials\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:32:- create mock OAuth authorization codes through browser login and consent with explicit endpoint permission selection\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:38:- external OAuth provider integration\\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:42:- full MCP resources, prompts, sampling, elicitation, or task-augmented execution in MVP\\ndocs/PRODUCT_S